  "response_text": "Here's a healthy breakfast plan for a week, featuring a variety of nutritious options to keep your mornings exciting and balanced:\n\n### Day 1: Overnight Oats\n- **Ingredients**: Rolled oats, almond milk, chia seeds, honey, sliced banana, and walnuts.\n- **Preparation**: Mix 1/2 cup oats, 1 cup almond milk, 1 tbsp chia seeds, and 1 tsp honey in a jar. Refrigerate overnight. In the morning, top with sliced banana and walnuts.\n\n### Day 2: Greek Yogurt Parfait\n- **Ingredients**: Greek yogurt, mixed berries (strawberries, blueberries, raspberries), and granola.\n- **Preparation**: Layer 1 cup Greek yogurt with 1 cup mixed berries and 1/4 cup granola in a bowl or glass. Drizzle with honey if desired.\n\n### Day 3: Avocado Toast\n- **Ingredients**: Whole grain bread, ripe avocado, cherry tomatoes, salt, pepper, and a poached egg (optional).\n- **Preparation**: Toast 1 slice of whole grain bread. Mash 1/2 an avocado and spread it on the toast. Top with halved cherry tomatoes, salt, pepper, and a poached egg if desired.\n\n### Day 4: Smoothie Bowl\n- **Ingredients**: Spinach, banana, almond milk, protein powder, and toppings (sliced fruit, nuts, seeds).\n- **Preparation**: Blend 1 cup spinach, 1 banana, and 1 cup almond milk until smooth. Pour into a bowl and top with sliced fruit, nuts, and seeds.\n\n### Day 5: Quinoa Breakfast Bowl\n- **Ingredients**: Cooked quinoa, almond milk, cinnamon, honey, sliced apple, and almonds.\n- **Preparation**: Heat 1 cup cooked quinoa with 1/2 cup almond milk, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, and 1 tsp honey. Top with sliced apple and a handful of almonds.\n\n### Day 6: Egg and Veggie Scramble\n- **Ingredients**: Eggs, spinach, bell peppers, onions, tomatoes, and feta cheese.\n- **Preparation**: Scramble 2 eggs in a pan with chopped veggies (spinach, bell peppers, onions, tomatoes) until cooked. Add crumbled feta cheese before serving.\n\n### Day 7: Chia Seed Pudding\n- **Ingredients**: Chia seeds, coconut milk, vanilla extract, honey, and fresh fruit.\n- **Preparation**: Mix 1/4 cup chia seeds with 1 cup coconut milk, 1 tsp vanilla extract, and 1 tbsp honey. Refrigerate overnight. In the morning, top with fresh fruit.\n\n### Tips for Preparation:\n- Prep ingredients the night before for quick assembly in the morning.\n- Feel free to swap ingredients based on your preferences or dietary needs.\n- Stay hydrated with a glass of water or herbal tea alongside your breakfast.\n\nEnjoy your healthy breakfasts!",
